well i'm in guam right now. it is soooo hot here. like at 6am it is alread 85 degrees. the water is like being in a jacuzzi. i went snorkling and saw so many pretty fish. this island is the vacation place for the Japanese. they are everywhere. tourists. my little brother is soo cute. he loves me. he won't even go to my dad and give him a a hug. he comes to me. :). he is so cute. they have a baha'i center here. baha'i is actually a popular religion here. adelia will be happy. i know. when you are on the road you look to your left and you see crystal clear blue waters everywhere. it is so beautiful. but there are dangerous reefs out there. many people die from the reefs and the current. guam is basically a mountain. the frist couple of feet off the shore are quite shallow but once you hit the waves they drag you in and you are in thousand feet deep water. its like and under water cliff. its pretty neat. there only animals here are geikos, snakes, pigs, goat, water buffalo, chicken, and bugs. ive seen all of those wild. its so cool. well to me. the people here are quite obese. i think it is because of the heat. did i mention its really hot here. well ill be back in the states thursday. im leaving tokyo on june 15th at 3pm and arrive in detroit on june 15th at 1:45pm.. hehe i'll be back in the country and hour and fifteen minutes BEFORE i left. its a 13 hour plane ride. isnt that crazy. im tmie traveling. lol! peace out.

ps hope the tropical depression coming your guys' way doesnt hurt too bad.   :)

Lately things are coming in perspective.  I've learned alot that I have never even considered thinking about.  Everything is peaceful yet corrupted.  I don't know why people have to be so judgemental about everyone else.  I guess human nature tends to be like that.  If not then what's perfect?  I just wish that things would never have to go badly.  But it's like the respiratory system.  Positive and negative charges.  Up vs down, happy vs sad, better vs worse, live vs die, good vs evil.  Cycles run everything.  There is no straight line that one can follow.  No real path.  There will always be obstacles.  I don't want it but it's there.  I quit crew.  Takes too much of my time.  I need a job.  Money in my life will always run my mother.  I need to help her because she needs me.  I feel bad but it's the cycle.  It will come back to me in some form.  Peace out.

I am thinking it's a sign that the freckles
In our eyes are mirror images and when
We kiss they're perfectly aligned
And I have to speculate that God himself
Did make us into corresponding shapes like
Puzzle pieces from the clay
True, it may seem like a stretch, but
Its thoughts like this that catch my troubled
Head when you're away when I am missing you to death
When you are out there on the road for
Several weeks of shows and when you scan
The radio, I hope this song will guide you home

They will see us waving from such great
Heights, 'come down now,' they'll say
But everything looks perfect from far away,
'come down now,' but we'll stay...

I tried my best to leave this all on your
Machine but the persistent beat it sounded
Thin upon listening
That frankly will not fly. you will hear
The shrillest highs and lowest lows with
The windows down when this is guiding you home

I am happy to say that I have finished poisonwood bible and that it is the greatest book in the world, well one of them. peace out.
